<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4736159>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figs 3–9. 3–6. Apomyrsidea klimesi (Sychra in Sychra et al., 2006) gen. et comb. nov. (CR15). 3. Dorsal view of head, prothorax and mesothorax of female. 4. Prosternal plate of female. 5. Metasternal plate and sternites I–III of female. 6. Male genitalia. – 7–9. Male genital sac sclerites. 7. A. klimesi gen. et comb. nov. 8. A. circumsternata (Valim & Weckstein, 2013) gen. et comb. nov. 9. A. isacantha (Valim & Weckstein, 2013) gen. et comb. nov. Abbreviations: a–b = head sensilla; dps = dorso-central pronotal setae; mps = marginal prothoracic setae; 8–30 = dorsal head setae. Figs 7–9 are drawn to the same scale." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4736159/files/figure.png" .

